  <h1>
   buffer_resize
  </h1>
  With this function you can resize a given buffer to be the size (in bytes) that you specify.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">buffer_resize(buffer, newsize);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      buffer
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Buffers/buffer_create.htm">
        Buffer ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the buffer to change the size of.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      newsize
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The new size of the buffer (in bytes).
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if (buffer_get_size(buff) &amp;amp;lt; 16384)
{
    buffer_resize(buff, 16384);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check the size of the buffer indexed in the variable "buff" and if it is less than the given value, the buffer is resized.
